.TH mp 1  "mp 0.8.11" 
.SH NAME
mp \- Connect to a moshpits server
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmp\fR [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]... [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR]... [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-config\-absolute\-path\fR] [\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-\-tracing\-absolute\-path\fR] [\fB\-p\fR|\fB\-\-private\-key\-path\fR] [\fB\-k\fR|\fB\-\-public\-key\-path\fR] [\fB\-s\fR|\fB\-\-server\-port\fR] [\fB\-\-predict\fR] [\fB\-\-nat\-warmup\fR] [\fB\-\-nat\-warmup\-count\fR] [\fB\-\-diff\-mode\fR] [\fB\-\-kex\-algos\fR] [\fB\-\-aead\-algos\fR] [\fB\-\-mac\-algos\fR] [\fB\-\-kdf\-algos\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fISERVER_DESTINATION\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Connect to a moshpits server
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Turn up logging verbosity (multiple will turn it up more)
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Turn down logging verbosity (multiple will turn it down more)
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\-absolute\-path\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Specify the absolute path to the config file
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-tracing\-absolute\-path\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Specify the absolute path to the tracing output file
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-private\-key\-path\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Specify the absolute path to the private key file
.TP
\fB\-k\fR, \fB\-\-public\-key\-path\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Specify the absolute path to the public key file
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-server\-port\fR \fI<PORT>\fR [default: 40404]
The port number of the server to connect to (default: 40404)
.TP
\fB\-\-predict\fR \fI<MODE>\fR [default: adaptive]
Local\-echo prediction: adaptive (default), always, or never
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
adaptive
.IP \(bu 2
always
.IP \(bu 2
never
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-nat\-warmup\fR
Send NAT warmup keepalives at UDP session start (opt\-in)
.TP
\fB\-\-nat\-warmup\-count\fR \fI<N>\fR [default: 3]
Number of NAT warmup keepalives to send (default: 3)
.TP
\fB\-\-diff\-mode\fR \fI<MODE>\fR [default: reliable]
UDP diff transport mode: reliable (default), datagram, or statesync
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
reliable
.IP \(bu 2
datagram
.IP \(bu 2
statesync
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-kex\-algos\fR \fI<ALGOS>\fR
Ordered KEX algorithms to offer, comma\-separated [supported: x25519\-sha256 (default), ml\-kem\-768\-sha256, ml\-kem\-512\-sha256, ml\-kem\-1024\-sha256, p384\-sha384, p256\-sha256]
.TP
\fB\-\-aead\-algos\fR \fI<ALGOS>\fR
Ordered AEAD algorithms to offer, comma\-separated [supported: aes256\-gcm\-siv (default), aes256\-gcm, chacha20\-poly1305, aes128\-gcm\-siv]
.TP
\fB\-\-mac\-algos\fR \fI<ALGOS>\fR
Ordered MAC algorithms to offer, comma\-separated [supported: hmac\-sha512 (default), hmac\-sha256]
.TP
\fB\-\-kdf\-algos\fR \fI<ALGOS>\fR
Ordered KDF algorithms to offer, comma\-separated [supported: hkdf\-sha256 (default), hkdf\-sha384, hkdf\-sha512]
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.TP
<\fISERVER_DESTINATION\fR>
The IP address of the server to connect to (user@address or address)
.SH VERSION
v0.8.11
